Reading time late in afternoon due to amount of boat traffic safety. reading sent to the great 1996 secchi dip-in Ohio. lake restricted to no wake between 4 p.m. and 11 a.m.  Lake level: very high
Beautiful day- air temp is 89 degrees- slight wind- not too much traffic.
Perfect fall day- no ice- 70 degrees air temp- very slight wind.
Weather was excellent.  Slight wind and 62 degrees.  Ice off for two weeks.  Eurasian milfoil still present with no regression.
Greenish blue.  Quiet- beautiful day with little blooms on the lake.  Air temperature around 70 degrees.  The dnr's control of Eurasian milfoil seems to working or just wishful thinking.
Water blue green.  Another beautiful week day.  Some erosion along some shores most likely due to boats coming too close when starting to accelerate.
Sunny- 70 deg- light wind- no loons today.
Sunny- 66 deg.- light N wind- bobcat machine noise in background.
Sunny- 84 deg.- very light wind- lots of rain this week.
Sunny- 76 deg.- light wind- 2.5" rain on 8/19.
Partly sunny- 52 F- no wind- air temp 35 F this morning- beautiful fall colors.
Mostly cloudy- 58 deg. F- moderate wind
Sunny- the temperature is in the 50s- windy- and no loon.
Partly sunny- the temperature is in the 70s- moderate wind- and motor will not start.
Sunny- the temperature is 80 degrees- light wind- beautiful weather- and motor sputtered.
Sunny- the temperature is in the 70s- no wind- beautiful day- and motor still sputtering.
Sunny- light wind- temperature in the 50s- and no clouds.
Partly sunny- moderate wind. 60 F. Iceout 4-11-02
moderate wind- clear skies- temp in the 80's.
sunny- wind 10-15 mph- 50 F- did not see loon.
mostly sunny- sl. to mod. wind- 78 F- lawnmower noise.
Sunny- 60 F- Sl wind.  Ice out 4/8/2005.
Sunny- 70 F.  Moderate wind.  Ice out 3-31-2006.
Aided by Roger Perenick and Gloria Johanns
aided by Gloria Johanns; mbig blue sky
Sunny/partly cloudy.  Lots of rain causing more turbulence in lake.
